<p>Which is kind of interesting (time for some philosophy): would you like immortality? I mean obviously yes, but when you think about it for a while if we are immortals then there will be no urgency to anything no eagerness, if I don‚Äôt meet you today I‚Äôll meet you next month or maybe in the next 700 years, if I don‚Äôt do it now I‚Äôll just do it later or next year or next century.
