<p>Studying in a university as unstable as university of Khartoum I have experienced how plenty of time  can be counterproductive, whenever it‚Äôs closed I have this urge to learn new skills or improve the ones I have, But soon as I realize that I have more time and no deadlines  every today s becomes tomorrow and every tomorrow becomes next week until couple months down the road I wish you started few months earlier then you start self loathing and being depressed about it leading you to waste even more time .</p>

<p>I (and similar to a lot of people) got one thing about productivity wrong. I thought I have to be in my best physical and mental state to be productive, but the truth is -a least for me- is that productivity what‚Äôs really gives me good feelings it‚Äôs hard to get started when you are not motivated but once I actually set down and start working on something I end up being much happier and satisfied.</p>

